org.sbml.jsbml.validator.offline.constraints

Interface ConstraintDeclaration

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractConstraintDeclaration, AlgebraicRuleConstraints, ArraysSBasePluginConstraints, AssignmentConstraints, AssignmentRuleConstraints, ASTNodeConstraints, CompartmentConstraints, CompartmentReferenceConstraints, CompartmentTypeConstraints, ConstraintConstraints, DelayConstraints, DimensionConstraints, EventAssignmentConstraints, EventConstraints, ExplicitRuleConstraints, FunctionDefinitionConstraints, IndexConstraints, InitialAssignmentConstraints, KineticLawConstraints, LayoutConstraints, LocalParameterConstraints, MathContainerConstraints, ModelConstraints, MultiCompartmentPluginConstraints, ParameterConstraints, PriorityConstraints, RateRuleConstraints, ReactionConstraints, RuleConstraints, SBaseConstraints, SBaseWithDerivedUnitConstraints, SBaseWithUnitConstraints, SBMLDocumentConstraints, SimpleSpeciesReferenceConstraints, SpeciesConstraints, SpeciesReferenceConstraints, SpeciesTypeConstraints, TreeNodeConstraints, TriggerConstraints, UnitConstraints, UnitDefinitionConstraints

    public interface ConstraintDeclaration
    Basic interface for constraint declarations. If you want to provide constraints for a custom class, consider to inherit from AbstractConstraintDeclaration instead. This abstract class has already a working implementation of most of the methods and supports caching
    Since:
    1.2
    Author:
    Roman
    See Also:
    AbstractConstraintDeclaration
    Last modified:
    04.08.2016

      • createConstraints

        <T> ConstraintGroup<T> createConstraints(int level,
                                         int version,
                                         String attributeName)
        Creates all the constraints which are needed to validate the attribute in the given level and version of SBML. This should only be error codes which refer to a error with severities SBMLError.SEVERITY.ERROR or SBMLError.SEVERITY.FATAL.
        Parameters:
        level -
        version -
        categories -
        Returns:
        A ConstraintGroup with at least 1 member or null if no constraint was loaded
